NO CONTEST plea entered to count 1, PTC possess cocaine.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismis and read in count 2.  Motion granted.
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for a period of twelve (12) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) AODA assessment and follow through;
2) submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) maintain absolute sobriety;
4) maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
5) pay court costs;
6) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
The Court orders expungement under Section 973.015 upon successful completion of the sentence.
Cash bail applied to costs.
